15 WHEREAS, as a former Human Resources Director in a small rural county, Tina embodies
16 true leadership and passion to advocate for those around her; and
17 WHEREAS, whether through advocacy, mentorship, or community organizing, Tina is
18 committed to ensuring that everyone has the opportunity to be heard and supported.
19 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
20 extraordinary servant leader be appropriately recognized.
21 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
22 the members of this body congratulate and commend Tina Thames for receiving the 2025
23 Yellow Rose Nikki T. Randall Servant Leader Award and extend best wishes for her
24 continued success.
25 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
26 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Tina
27 Thames.
